title: For Sale:  CMP Rare M1C Garand Sniper variant
postcontent:
Springfield 1953 M1 Garand with CMP cartouche.  Rifle was sold as a package deal with the Griffin & Howe M1c scope mount and 7/8" rings.  This mount is serialized to the rifle and mounted by Griffin and Howe.  Originally called the M1E7, the government actually sent these Garands out to custom gunmaker Griffin & Howe for a side-mounted removable sliding scope mount.  Griffen and Howe no longer produce the 7/8" rings, and only sell 1" currently.  This is an authentic period mount included on this rifle.

Rifle has removable M2 conical flash hider and MRT 1-52 M1 Garand leather cheek pad.  

The rifle alone without the mounting bracket and rings is available from the CMP for $3000.  The G&H mount is over $400, and needs to be custom fitted.  This rifle is set up ready to mount as a rare collectors piece or as a match shooters gun.  Rifle has rarely been shot, only enough to zero the scope.  

Rifle also included original Leopold and Stevens M84 telescope.  2.5x zoom.  Reproductions of this optic go for upwards of $400.  

Will include an ammo can of greek M1 ball and a few surplus clips
